From 89e2932b1164e5a72dc7c81bfa975b561341c80d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tushar Darote <tdarote@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 19:13:40 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] tflite: include 4-bit fully connected reference
 implementation in CMake build
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

TensorFlow Lite 2.16’s CMake build does not include
kernels/internal/optimized/4bit/fully_connected_reference.cc in
TFLITE_KERNEL_SRCS.

The corresponding header (fully_connected_reference.h) emits non-inline
4-bit fully connected helper symbols (e.g. ReferenceBatchQuantizeFloats4Bit),
which are required on ARMv7 when the reference implementation is selected.
Because the .cc file is not linked, CMake-based builds fail with undefined
reference errors, while Bazel builds succeed.

Explicitly append fully_connected_reference.cc to TFLITE_KERNEL_SRCS to
restore link completeness. This matches Bazel behavior and does not change
runtime behavior.

This issue is exposed on ARMv7; ARMv8 typically selects the NEON path and
does not require the reference implementation.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [TensorFlow Lite 2.16.x is no longer maintained upstream; the issue is resolved in later releases via refactoring]
Signed-off-by: Tushar Darote <tdarote@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 tensorflow/lite/CMakeLists.txt | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/tensorflow/lite/CMakeLists.txt b/tensorflow/lite/CMakeLists.txt
index 2861aff5103..68a93b8480e 100644
--- a/tensorflow/lite/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/tensorflow/lite/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -534,6 +534,9 @@ populate_tflite_source_vars("kernels"
   TFLITE_KERNEL_SRCS
   FILTER "(.*_test_util_internal|test_.*|.*_ops_wrapper)\\.(cc|h)"
 )
+list(APPEND TFLITE_KERNEL_SRCS
+  ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/kernels/internal/optimized/4bit/fully_connected_reference.cc
+)
 populate_tflite_source_vars("kernels/internal" TFLITE_KERNEL_INTERNAL_SRCS)
 populate_tflite_source_vars("kernels/internal/optimized"
   TFLITE_KERNEL_INTERNAL_OPT_SRCS
-- 
2.34.1

